CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 3, 1957, pg. A10 reads: "A Hat?? - This fresh vegetable hat, made by Mrs. Rachel Brown, won first prize at a recent hat show sponsored by the NAACP Women's Auxiliary. The hat is made of cabbage leaves, carrots and radishes. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Rachel Brown wearing hat made from cabbage leaves, carrots, and radishes, for NAACP Women's Auxiliary Novel Hat Show
